Already 10 weeks since the last post - what is wrong with me? :D I thought a lot about social media, Instagram and the business behind it. I came to the conclusion that the only thing I want to present here is my art. I know a lot of you are only following me for my landscape photos and that is totally fine :) but since I started this account a few years ago my photography changed a lot! I created many other accounts to show the different type of photos I take but I think I'm going to post it all here on my main account haha. We will see how this works out üòä so stay safe and have a nice day/night üôèüèª big thanks to all the people that are still here and supporting me.

Hey guys today I released my second EP called "Healing Herbs" on Spotify. The EP contains 5 very chill & relaxing tracks - And yes I know a lot of you are not interested into hearing the music since this is an landscape based account :D but music for me is just as important as my photography so if you are interested in checking out my music you can find & click the link in my Instagram Profile :) thanks for your time and have a great weekend ‚ù§

So yeah... over 6 month break from this account ..after beeing active for over 4 years on Instagram it doesn't feel that long to be honest. I think today social media has a heavy influence on our lifes and I realized how depending you get from it. The past months I also learned a lot about myself, my goals and what I want to do with my life. I think some of you know that my other big passion is making music. The last 6 months I did nothing than working and making music and since I'm working for a big photo studio the motivation for my personal photography came a bit short. But my goal this year is to start taking more photos for myself again.
But since music is my big passion it would be awesome if you could follow me on this new journey too :)
So for everyone that is also interested in my music or me as a person feel free to follow my second account @iamstonii .
There I post me making my lofi hiphop/ chillhop beats, film photography or some other stuff about my life. Thanks for reading ‚ù§
